{
  "text": "Serum IGF-1/IGFBP-3 ratio was significantly lower in lung cancer patients with nodal and distant metastasis. Although IGF-1/IGFBP-3 ratio in ELF did not show any significant correlation with the stage of lung cancer, IGF-1/IGFBP-3 ratio in serum was found to be negatively correlated with the stage. It has been known that IGFBP-3 regulates IGF-1 activity and also cell growth and apoptosis. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] There is a negative correlation between serum IGFBP-3 levels and prostate, lung, colon cancer risk and this suggests a protective role of IGFBP-3 against the effects of systemic IGF-1. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Thus, in lung cancer the balance between IGF-1and IGFBP-3 might be important in the progression of the disease. The mechanism of this is unclear and it should be investigated by further studies.",
  "correct_citation": {
